Malaysia Offers New Tax Incentives to Iskandar Region Investors

-- B y   M a n i r a j a n   R a m a s a m y
-- 
2011-05-05T08:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/malaysia-offers-new-tax-incentives-to-iskandar-region-investors.html
Investors in  Malaysia ’s southern
Iskandar regional development zone will be offered a new package
on incentives, including a package of tax breaks, Prime Minister
Najib Razak said in a statement today.  Companies newly investing more than 10 million ringgit,
excluding land costs, in the services sector may qualify for
corporate  tax exemption  for five years, as well as import and
sales duty incentives for certain machinery and equipment, the
statement said. There will also be flexibility from full
compliance with the central bank’s foreign exchange rules and
recruitment of foreign knowledge workers, it said.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Manirajan Ramasamy in Kuala Lumpur at 
 rmanirajan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Barry Porter in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
 bporter10@bloomberg.net . 